                            <comment id="14633890" author="roboduke" created="Wed, 13 Dec 2023 02:37:19 -0800"  >A pull request was submitted for review.&lt;br/&gt;
URL: &lt;a href=&quot;https://git.openjdk.org/jdk21u-dev/pull/5&quot;&gt;https://git.openjdk.org/jdk21u-dev/pull/5&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Date: 2023-12-13 10:30:13 +0000</comment>
                            <comment id="14629117" author="JIRAUSER19812" created="Mon, 27 Nov 2023 09:32:29 -0800"  >CSR was created retroactively</comment>
                            <comment id="14629102" author="shade" created="Mon, 27 Nov 2023 08:55:33 -0800"  >Weeeell, we can go this full CSR dance, but I see this compatibility concern was not raised during the initial integration. Should Angelos then submit one retroactively for JDK 22 with both 22 and 21 as Fix-Versions?&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
That said, my understanding is that we make compiler reject programs that are required to be rejected by spec. Given that we expect people trying to compile their programs with JDK 21 in the nearest future, starting to reject things today is better than rejecting things later. (This should be discussed in CSR, if we really go that way.)</comment>
                            <comment id="14629097" author="robm" created="Mon, 27 Nov 2023 08:37:43 -0800"  >[~shade] After some discussion we would like to see this issue get CSR (&lt;a href=&quot;https://wiki.openjdk.org/display/csr/Main&quot;&gt;https://wiki.openjdk.org/display/csr/Main&lt;/a&gt;) approval prior to backporting it to an update release.</comment>
                            <comment id="14627659" author="mcimadamore" created="Mon, 20 Nov 2023 08:34:20 -0800"  >Note: this fix changes the space of compilable programs: programs that used to compile correctly will now fail to compile. In general we avoid backporting compiler fixes that alter the compilable space in incompatible ways.</comment>
                            <comment id="14626848" author="roboduke" created="Thu, 16 Nov 2023 04:13:55 -0800"  >A pull request was submitted for review.&lt;br/&gt;
URL: &lt;a href=&quot;https://git.openjdk.org/jdk21u/pull/369&quot;&gt;https://git.openjdk.org/jdk21u/pull/369&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Date: 2023-11-16 12:06:41 +0000</comment>
                            <comment id="14626847" author="roboduke" created="Thu, 16 Nov 2023 04:09:09 -0800"  >[jdk21u-fix-request] Approval Request from Aleksey Shipil&amp;#xEB;v&lt;br/&gt;
